PrecisRegulations Amending the FOOD AND DRUG REGULATIONS (997 - CANADIAN WHISKY) by revising the compositional standard for Canadian Whisky (also known as Canadian Rye Whisky or Rye Whisky) to the extent that it must contain a minimum alcohol content of 40 percent by volume and that all aging of this product must be conducted in Canada.
